Correctness_Score: 1.0
Style_Score: 0.6
Simplicity_Score: 1.0
Robustness_Score: 0.9
Reasoning: The implementation matches the logical reduction (minimal k is the first k where the sum of top-k sweetnesses > X or top-k saltinesses > Y) and passed the provided samples plus 500 random brute-force checks for small N, so I give full correctness. The code is concise with clear variable names and a few inline comments but lacks a module docstring and more explanatory comments, hence a moderate style score. The approach is minimal and efficient (two sorts and linear scans, O(N log N)), so it scores perfectly for simplicity. It correctly handles edge cases (including thresholds that never trigger and small N) and is maintainable, so I give a high robustness score.
